# Objective

Evaluate conflicting research findings on the same topic. Identify possible reasons for disagreement, assess the strength of the available evidence, and produce a balanced conclusion that accurately reflects the current state of research.

---

# Research Question

> Does consuming coffee improve cognitive performance?

---

# Research Findings

## Study A

A randomized controlled trial involving 300 healthy adults found that moderate caffeine intake improved attention, reaction time, and short-term memory during cognitive tests.

---

## Study B

A meta-analysis of 25 studies concluded that caffeine consistently improves alertness but has only a small and inconsistent effect on memory and higher-level cognitive functions.

---

## Study C

A longitudinal study following 2,000 adults over eight years found no meaningful long-term relationship between daily coffee consumption and overall cognitive performance.

